User data section.


1. EC2

Enable public IP Address (Yes for public)

#!/bin/bash     
sudo su     
yum update -y       
yum install httpd -y            
echo "<html><h1> Welcome to Whizlabs Server 1 </h1><html>" > /var/www/html/index.html               
systemctl start httpd       
systemctl enable httpd	 - PRAN Card & self-attested Pan Card are mandatory documents required for SA To NPS.


2. ECS Load balancer

Security Group for both Load balancer and ECS

ECS Security Group allows from ALB Security Group

Target group can be created without targets and assigned to Loadbalancer.  And later assign the target

ECS Cluster - Require the instance and Key pair

Under Container - 1

Container name: Enter httpd
Image: enter httpd:2.4 (make sure no extra space is given)


3. S3 - Cloudfront

Object Ownership: Select ACLs enabled option and choose Object writer as Object owner

{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "Statement1",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": {
                "AWS": "*"
            },
            "Action": "s3:*",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::whizlabs123456789"
        }
    ]
}


Cloudfront - setup error(404)/block(based on geographic 403) in the distribution


4. ec2 basic

sudo su
yum -y update



login to private ec2\
chmod 400 MyKey.pem
ssh  ec2-user@<Private IP of MyPrivateEC2Server> -i MyKey.pem
sudo su
yum -y update



